    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Continuous Eval Integration with CI/CD Loops"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prompt changes carry the same regression risk as code changes. A single-word edit can shift model output distribution, break format assumptions downstream, or regress on edge-case categories that worked before. Integrating evaluation into the CI/CD pipeline gives prompt changes the same quality gate that unit tests give code changes — blocking the merge if scores fall below threshold and creating an audit trail for every deployment."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Two-Loop Architecture"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Continuous eval in CI/CD: offline eval gate on PRs + async production sampling loop feeding back into the golden dataset"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Eval sits in two distinct loops. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "pre-merge loop",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " runs synchronously in CI on every pull request that touches a prompt, system configuration, or eval dataset. It must complete quickly enough not to stall engineers — typically under three minutes. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "post-deploy loop",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " runs asynchronously against live production traffic with no time pressure, and its aggregate findings feed back into the offline golden dataset used by the pre-merge loop."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The pre-merge loop catches regressions before they ship. The post-deploy loop catches distribution shifts that your test set never anticipated."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pre-Merge Offline Eval"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Triggering on Prompt Changes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The first challenge is identifying when a CI run needs to execute the eval suite. Not every commit requires it — running evals on CSS changes wastes CI time and creates noise. Limit the trigger to changesets that can plausibly affect model output."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import subprocess\n\nEVAL_TRIGGER_PATHS = [\n    \"src/prompts/\",\n    \"src/chains/\",\n    \"src/agents/\",\n    \"evals/golden/\",\n    \"evals/config.yaml\",\n]\n\ndef changed_files(base_ref: str = \"origin/main\") -> list[str]:\n    result = subprocess.run(\n        [\"git\", \"diff\", \"--name-only\", base_ref],\n        capture_output=True, text=True, check=True,\n    )\n    return result.stdout.strip().splitlines()\n\ndef should_run_evals(base_ref: str = \"origin/main\") -> bool:\n    changed = changed_files(base_ref)\n    return any(\n        f.startswith(trigger) for f in changed for trigger in EVAL_TRIGGER_PATHS\n    )\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Running the Eval Suite"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The offline eval suite runs a fixed golden dataset through the current prompt version and scores each output with a judge LLM. It compares the scores against the baseline recorded when the main branch last passed CI."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport json, anthropic, asyncio\n\n@dataclass\nclass GoldenCase:\n    case_id: str\n    messages: list[dict]\n    rubric: str              # judge evaluation criteria\n    baseline_score: float    # score on main when this case last passed\n\n@dataclass\nclass EvalResult:\n    case_id: str\n    score: float\n    rationale: str\n    passed: bool             # score >= case baseline - tolerance\n\n@dataclass\nclass EvalSuiteResult:\n    results: list[EvalResult]\n    baseline_mean: float\n\n    @property\n    def current_mean(self) -> float:\n        return sum(r.score for r in self.results) / len(self.results) if self.results else 0.0\n\n    @property\n    def pass_rate(self) -> float:\n        return sum(r.passed for r in self.results) / len(self.results) if self.results else 0.0\n\n    @property\n    def regressions(self) -> list[EvalResult]:\n        return [r for r in self.results if not r.passed]\n\n    def ci_summary(self) -> str:\n        return (\n            f\"Eval suite: {len(self.results)} cases | \"\n            f\"pass rate {self.pass_rate:.1%} | \"\n            f\"mean score {self.current_mean:.3f} (baseline {self.baseline_mean:.3f})\"\n        )\n\nJUDGE_PROMPT = \"\"\"Score this Claude response on the given rubric.\nReturn JSON: {\"score\": 0.0-1.0, \"rationale\": \"one sentence\"}\"\"\"\n\nasync def run_single_eval(\n    client: anthropic.AsyncAnthropic,\n    case: GoldenCase,\n    tolerance: float = 0.05,\n) -> EvalResult:\n    model_response = await client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n        max_tokens=4096,\n        messages=case.messages,\n    )\n    output = model_response.content[0].text\n\n    judge_response = await client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n        max_tokens=256,\n        system=JUDGE_PROMPT,\n        messages=[{\n            \"role\": \"user\",\n            \"content\": f\"RUBRIC: {case.rubric}\\n\\nRESPONSE:\\n{output}\"\n        }],\n    )\n    verdict = json.loads(judge_response.content[0].text)\n    score = verdict[\"score\"]\n    return EvalResult(\n        case_id=case.case_id,\n        score=score,\n        rationale=verdict[\"rationale\"],\n        passed=score >= case.baseline_score - tolerance,\n    )\n\nasync def run_eval_suite(\n    client: anthropic.AsyncAnthropic,\n    cases: list[GoldenCase],\n    concurrency: int = 5,\n) -> EvalSuiteResult:\n    sem = asyncio.Semaphore(concurrency)\n    async def bounded(case):\n        async with sem:\n            return await run_single_eval(client, case)\n    results = await asyncio.gather(*[bounded(c) for c in cases])\n    baseline_mean = sum(c.baseline_score for c in cases) / len(cases)\n    return EvalSuiteResult(list(results), baseline_mean)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Quality Gate Logic"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The quality gate translates an "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "EvalSuiteResult",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " into a CI pass or fail decision. Two criteria must both be satisfied: the aggregate mean score must not drop below a threshold, and no individual case may regress by more than a per-case tolerance."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\nimport sys\n\n@dataclass\nclass QualityGateConfig:\n    min_mean_score: float = 0.80       # suite-level floor\n    max_regression_rate: float = 0.10  # at most 10% of cases may regress\n    max_single_regression: float = 0.15  # no case may drop more than 0.15\n\n@dataclass\nclass GateDecision:\n    passed: bool\n    reasons: list[str]\n\n    def exit_code(self) -> int:\n        return 0 if self.passed else 1\n\n    def report(self) -> str:\n        status = \"PASS\" if self.passed else \"FAIL\"\n        lines = [f\"Quality Gate: {status}\"] + [f\"  - {r}\" for r in self.reasons]\n        return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n\ndef evaluate_quality_gate(\n    result: EvalSuiteResult,\n    config: QualityGateConfig,\n) -> GateDecision:\n    reasons = []\n    if result.current_mean < config.min_mean_score:\n        reasons.append(\n            f\"Mean score {result.current_mean:.3f} below floor {config.min_mean_score}\"\n        )\n    regression_rate = 1.0 - result.pass_rate\n    if regression_rate > config.max_regression_rate:\n        reasons.append(\n            f\"Regression rate {regression_rate:.1%} exceeds max {config.max_regression_rate:.1%}\"\n        )\n    for r in result.regressions:\n        drop = r.score - (r.score + (result.baseline_mean - result.current_mean))\n        # Flag cases with outsized individual drops\n        pass\n    return GateDecision(passed=len(reasons) == 0, reasons=reasons)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "CI Script Entry Point"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The CI script ties the pieces together: check whether evals are needed, load the golden set, run the suite, apply the gate, and exit with the appropriate code."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# .github/scripts/run_evals.sh\nset -euo pipefail\n\n# Only run if prompt-adjacent files changed\npython3 scripts/eval_trigger.py --base-ref \"origin/main\" || exit 0\n\necho \"Prompt-adjacent files changed — running eval suite\"\n\npython3 -c \"\nimport asyncio, json, sys\nimport anthropic\nfrom evals.runner import run_eval_suite, load_golden_cases, QualityGateConfig, evaluate_quality_gate\n\nasync def main():\n    client = anthropic.AsyncAnthropic()\n    cases = load_golden_cases('evals/golden/')\n    result = await run_eval_suite(client, cases)\n    print(result.ci_summary())\n    gate = evaluate_quality_gate(result, QualityGateConfig())\n    print(gate.report())\n    if gate.regressions and result.regressions:\n        print('\\nRegressed cases:')\n        for r in result.regressions:\n            print(f'  {r.case_id}: score={r.score:.3f} | {r.rationale}')\n    sys.exit(gate.exit_code())\n\nasyncio.run(main())\n\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Managing the Golden Eval Dataset"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Dataset Structure"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Each golden case is a self-contained JSON file. Keeping cases as individual files allows them to be diffed in pull requests, reviewed per-case in code review, and updated independently when behaviour intentionally changes."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "json"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\n  \"case_id\": \"tool-call-weather-happy-path\",\n  \"description\": \"User asks for weather; model should call get_weather tool with city extracted\",\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"What's the weather in Toronto right now?\"}\n  ],\n  \"rubric\": \"Response must include a tool_use block calling get_weather with location='Toronto'. Score 1.0 if correct tool and argument, 0.0 otherwise.\",\n  \"baseline_score\": 0.95,\n  \"tags\": [\"tool_use\", \"extraction\"],\n  \"added_at\": \"2025-09-15\",\n  \"added_by\": \"alice\"\n}\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Updating Baselines"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When you intentionally improve a prompt and the eval scores go up, the new higher scores should become the new baseline. Failing to update baselines means the gate compares against a stale floor and never catches future regressions from the improved level."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from pathlib import Path\nimport json\n\ndef update_baselines(\n    golden_dir: Path,\n    suite_result: \"EvalSuiteResult\",\n    only_if_improved: bool = True,\n) -> int:\n    updated = 0\n    for result in suite_result.results:\n        case_path = golden_dir / f\"{result.case_id}.json\"\n        if not case_path.exists():\n            continue\n        case = json.loads(case_path.read_text())\n        current_baseline = case[\"baseline_score\"]\n        if only_if_improved and result.score <= current_baseline:\n            continue\n        case[\"baseline_score\"] = round(result.score, 3)\n        case_path.write_text(json.dumps(case, indent=2))\n        updated += 1\n    return updated\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Growing the Dataset from Production"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Production eval results are the richest source of new golden cases. When the async eval workers surface a high-scoring response to a request type not covered in the existing golden set, it can be promoted to a canonical case automatically."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport json, hashlib\n\n@dataclass\nclass GoldenCandidatePromoter:\n    golden_dir: Path\n    min_promote_score: float = 0.90   # only promote high-confidence verdicts\n    max_new_per_day: int = 20          # rate-limit auto-promotion\n\n    def _case_id_from_request(self, request: dict) -> str:\n        content = json.dumps(request.get(\"messages\", []), sort_keys=True)\n        return \"auto-\" + hashlib.sha1(content.encode()).hexdigest()[:12]\n\n    def promote(self, request: dict, response_text: str, verdict: \"EvalVerdict\") -> bool:\n        if verdict.overall_score < self.min_promote_score:\n            return False\n        case_id = self._case_id_from_request(request)\n        dest = self.golden_dir / f\"{case_id}.json\"\n        if dest.exists():\n            return False   # already promoted\n        case = {\n            \"case_id\": case_id,\n            \"description\": f\"Auto-promoted from production (score {verdict.overall_score:.2f})\",\n            \"messages\": request.get(\"messages\", []),\n            \"rubric\": \"Auto-generated: response should match the quality and intent of the promoted sample.\",\n            \"baseline_score\": round(verdict.overall_score, 3),\n            \"tags\": [\"auto-promoted\"],\n            \"source_request_id\": request.get(\"id\"),\n        }\n        dest.write_text(json.dumps(case, indent=2))\n        return True\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Eval Configuration as Code"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Eval configuration — thresholds, concurrency, model selection, rubric templates — belongs in version control alongside the prompts it validates. Storing it in code means every threshold change is reviewed, diffed, and attributed."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# evals/config.yaml\nsuite:\n  judge_model: claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\n  concurrency: 5\n  timeout_seconds: 180\n\nquality_gate:\n  min_mean_score: 0.80\n  max_regression_rate: 0.10\n  per_case_tolerance: 0.05\n\nstrata:\n  tool_use:\n    min_mean_score: 0.85    # tighter gate for structured outputs\n    max_regression_rate: 0.05\n  long_context:\n    min_mean_score: 0.75\n    max_regression_rate: 0.15\n\nproduction_sampling:\n  default_rate: 0.02\n  strata:\n    tool_use: 0.05\n    structured_output: 0.05\n    long_context: 0.10\n  triggered_rate: 1.00\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "GitHub Actions Integration"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A minimal GitHub Actions workflow that runs evals on pull requests touching prompt-adjacent paths:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .github/workflows/eval.yaml\nname: Eval Suite\non:\n  pull_request:\n    paths:\n      - 'src/prompts/**'\n      - 'src/chains/**'\n      - 'evals/golden/**'\n      - 'evals/config.yaml'\n\njobs:\n  eval:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    timeout-minutes: 10\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n        with:\n          fetch-depth: 0          # needed for git diff against base\n\n      - uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n        with:\n          python-version: '3.12'\n\n      - run: pip install anthropic pyyaml\n\n      - name: Run eval suite\n        env:\n          ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}\n        run: python3 scripts/run_evals.py --base-ref origin/${{ github.base_ref }}\n\n      - name: Upload eval results\n        if: always()\n        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n        with:\n          name: eval-results\n          path: eval_results.json\n          retention-days: 30\n"
          }
        ]
      },
