      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Keeping Eval Fast"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The pre-merge eval suite must complete within your CI budget — engineers will disable a gate that takes 10 minutes per push. Several techniques keep eval latency manageable:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Run eval only when prompt-adjacent files change, not on every commit"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Maintain a fast tier (≤30 cases) and a thorough tier (full golden set); run only the fast tier in CI"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cache judge model responses keyed on (input, prompt hash) to avoid redundant API calls"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use concurrent judge calls (asyncio.gather with a Semaphore) to parallelise the golden set"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Set a per-case timeout so a single slow judge call cannot stall the whole suite"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Run the thorough tier on a nightly schedule rather than on every PR"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Continuous eval integration closes the quality feedback loop across the entire delivery cycle. Pre-merge offline evals block regressions before they reach production by running a judge LLM against a versioned golden dataset on every prompt-adjacent pull request. Post-deploy sampling monitors live traffic asynchronously and feeds novel high-quality cases back into the golden set. A shared eval config file keeps thresholds, model selection, and gate criteria in version control where they are reviewed and attributed like any other engineering decision. Together the two loops ensure that every prompt change is as rigorously validated as any code change."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
